[4] Global update: Polio Eradication Initiative
Date: Wed 10 Jul 2013
Source: Polio Eradication Initiative [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek.aspx


Global Polio Eradication Initiative update as of 10 Jul 2013
------------------------------------------------------------
Wild poliovirus (WPV) cases
Total cases: Year-to-date 2013 / Year-to-date 2012 / Total 2012
Globally: 108 / 91 / 223
- in endemic countries: 56 / 87 / 217
- in non-endemic countries: 52 / 4 / 6

Case breakdown by country
Countries: 2013 WPV1 / WPV3 / W1W3 / Total 2013 // 2012 WPV1 / WPV3 / W1W3 / Total year-to-date 2012 / Total 2012 // Date most recent case

Pakistan: 18 / 0 / 0 / 18 // 19 / 2 / 1 / 22 / 58 // 6 Jun 2013
Afghanistan: 3 / 0 / 0 / 3 // 10 / 0 / 0 / 10 / 37 // 6 Jun 2013
Nigeria: 35 / 0 / 0 / 35 // 41 / 13 / 0 / 54 / 122 // 18 Jun 2013
Somalia: 45 / 0 / 0 / 45 // 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 8 Jun 2013
Kenya: 7 / 0 / 0 / 7 // 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 3 Jun 2013
Chad: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 4 / 0 / 0 / 4 / 5 // 14 Jun 2012
Niger: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 15 Nov 2012
Total: 77 / 0 / 0 / 77 // 69 / 14 / 1 / 84 / 223
Total in endemic countries: 56 / 0 / 0 / 56 // 71 / 15 / 1 / 87 / 217
Total outbreak: 52 / 0 / 0 / 52 // 4 / 0 / 0 / 4 / 6

Data in WHO as of 10 Jul 2012 for 2012 data and 9 Jul 2013 for 2013 data.

- In the Horn of Africa, an outbreak of WPV1 is continuing, centred around Banadir, Somalia. The majority of cases associated with this outbreak developed paralysis before the start of the comprehensive emergency outbreak response activities.

- WPV3 continues to be at the lowest ever recorded levels. Globally, WPV3 has not been detected anywhere since November 2012, from Yobe state, Nigeria. In Asia, the strain has not been detected in over a year (since April 2012, from Khyber Agency in Pakistan). With the current historic low levels of WPV3, the world has a unique opportunity to rid itself of the 2nd strain of wild poliovirus (following the last case of WPV2 in 1999).

Afghanistan
-----------
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV cases for 2013 remains 3. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [6 Jun 2013] (WPV1 from Nangarhar).
- All 3 WPV cases this year [2013] were reported from Eastern Region, with links to both WPV1 in 2013 from neighbouring areas of Pakistan and WPV1 in 2012 from Afghanistan. In the high-risk Southern Region, no WPV cases have been reported since November 2012.
- Particular focus will be on immunizing mobile populations and Afghan populations on both sides of the border.
- No new cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases in 2013 remains 3. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [13 Mar 2013] (from Kandahar, Southern Region).

Nigeria
-------
- A total of 9 new WPV cases were reported in the past week, bringing the total number of WPV cases for 2013 to 35. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [18 Jun 2013] (WPV1 from Bauchi).
- No new cases of cVDPV2 were reported in the past week. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [24 Nov 2012] (from Kebbi).

Pakistan
--------
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV cases for 2013 remains 18. The most recent WPV case in the country had onset of paralysis on [6 Jun 2013] (WPV1 from Bara in Khyber Agency, Federally Administered Tribal Areas - FATA).
- No new cVDVP2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2013 remains 5. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [8 May 2013] (from Gadap town, greater Karachi, Sindh).
- FATA is the major WPV1 reservoir in Pakistan at the moment. Of 18 WPV1 cases reported in the country in 2013, more than half are from FATA. Bara in Khyber Agency is particularly affected. This outbreak is threatening progress achieved elsewhere in the country and in neighbouring Afghanistan.
- In 2011 and 2012, Bara was the epicentre of a major outbreak which also spread to other areas.

Central Africa: Chad and Cameroon
---------------------------------
- In Chad, no new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [14 Jun 2012] (WPV1 from Lac).
- However, one new cVDPV2 case was reported in the country, with onset of paralysis on [3 May 2013](from Kanem), bringing the total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2013 to 4.
- In Cameroon, no new cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2013 remains one (onset of paralysis on [9 May 2013] from Extreme-Nord).

Horn of Africa
--------------
- A total of 4 new WPV cases were reported in the past week (all from Banadir, Somalia), bringing the total number of WPV1 cases in the region to 52 (45 WPV1s from Somalia and 7 WPV1s from Kenya). The most recent case in the region had onset of paralysis on [8 Jun 2013] (from Banadir).
- Banadir remains the epicentre of the outbreak.
- Outbreak response across the Horn of Africa continues to be implemented. In Somalia, campaigns were held on [1-6 Jul 2013]. In Kenya, activities were conducted on [3-7 Jul 2013]. In Ethiopia on [5-8 Jul 2013], and in Yemen the next campaigns are planned for late August [2013].

West Africa
-----------
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The most recent case in the region was a WPV1 from Tahoua province in Niger with onset of paralysis on [15 Nov 2012].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since the last update (data from 26 Jun 2013), the total number of cases has increased by 31 cases -- from 77 to 108, with 20 additional cases reported in Somalia, 9 cases in Nigeria (all identified in the preceding week), and one case each in Pakistan and Kenya.

Using the reports of cVDPV cases (circulating vaccine derived poliovirus) in a country as an indicator of low vaccination coverages, the occurrence of these cases in Pakistan and Chad in recent months serves as a reminder that pockets of susceptibles still exist in these countries.

For the map of the world showing locations of polio cases, see http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek/Poliocasesworldwide.aspx. - Mod.MPP]
